	     <table class="mform"  border="0" cellpadding="1" cellspacing="0" width="100%" >
	     <form action="/cgi-bin/mrate.pl" name="f11193091814785">
	     <tr><td id="headerrow" colspan="2" class="mform" valign="top"><a id="sj" href="/db/item.html?item=14982&amp;mid=11193091814785">Drop Info for Windstones</a> <a id="fs8" href="/db/item.html?item=14982&amp;mid=11193091814785#post"><img src="/shared/reply_to_thread_ico.gif" border="0" alt="Reply..." width="17" height="11" /></a>
	     <br clear="all" /><small>Posted @ Mon, Jun 20th 7:10 PM 2005</small></td></tr>
	     <tr><td valign="top" id="fs8" class="mform"><span id="notbold">By:</span> <a href="/db/poster.html?user=119675"><span id="Guru">kirbyramz</span></a><br /><b><span id="Guru">Guru</span></b><br /><span id="notbold">158 posts<br /><span id="notbold">Score:</span> Excellent [4.88]</td><td valign=top class="mform" width="100%"><p>Ppl talk about getting 2 or four in an evening. I got about 40 in a few hours time. See below<br/>(below is my own repost)<br/>If you are after smithing ingredients and need a ton (literally) of arcrylia ore; then the place for you are the two grimling mining caves in Tenebrous Mtns.&nbsp;&nbsp;I just solo there and go back and forth from cave to cave. They repop in about the same time it takes me to clear both caves, so its pretty much non-stop farming. One good thing is that not only do they drop all the different sizes of acrylia ore, but they drop windstones about as often as the ore pieces/bricks/blocks. I quickly gathered up two stacks of windstones and got about 40 of the ores at the same time. Be sure to go there with empty bags or have good faction with town one zone over because you will also be getting tonz of those silly useless runes that sell for PP and lots of different Luclin vendor-type gems. Not to mention if you are after words/runes for spell making your bags will be filled up after like two rounds of clearing the caves. I hate having to leave a place once I have established a good farm spot, so I often 2-box another toon there to hold junk. There is no way you can get by without destorying hundreds of thier shiny (finesteel) wpn drops. Since they dont stack your bags will be full before one clearing if you wanted to loot them all. <br/>As far as smithing goes, you still need the wind essence to make the temper. I have found that it is a royal pain to try to get them from Tenebrous mtns. So many mobs roam and atk you that drop nothing you need that you spend most of your time clearing useless mobs. Then, when you do kill the ones you want (aliens) the drop rate on essences is very low. The same time I spent on farming ore and windstones when I got 80 of those, I spent also on essence and got 5. <br/>So your plan should be to head to Twilight sea to get essences. You can slaughter more and faster there and loot other needed stuff while you are at it.<br/><br/> <br/></p>&nbsp;<br /><span class=sm>----------------------------</span><br /><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=899422" target=_new>http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=899422</a><br/>EClapton<br/>70th Human Bard<br/>Leader, Holy Might Guild<br/>Seventh Hammer</td></tr>
